The paper deals with context-aware movie recommendation systems, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The analysis of the dataset involves machine learning techniques, which is a common theme in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of temporal information in the model suggests that the paper may also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The focus on user preferences and ratings may also place the paper in the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of household groupings in the dataset may suggest that the paper belongs to the social and economic networks (cs.SD) sub-category.
